text:
[music playing]
- Hi, I'm Webby.

And I'm so excited to
count down with you

four of my favorite
"DuckTales" disguises.

Starting my list at number four
is Don Karnage as Tom Karnage.

Any good spy can craft
the perfect disguise,

which is probably why
Don Carnage is bad at it.

Number three on my
list of top disguises

is from the best
super spy I know.
Mrs. Beakley is Darkwing Duck.

Granny meets the St.
Canardian Guardian?

It's the best combo since
peanut butter and crossbows.

Don't you mean peanut
butter and jelly?
No.

Even the worst villains get put
together the best disguises,

which is why number two
in my disguise countdown
is Mark Beaks as Mega-Beaks.

Beaks thought he could copy
the gizmo tech to become
as powerful as Gizmo Duck.

But he quickly found out he
messed with the wrong hero.

Top on my list of
favorite disguises

comes from the best
adventurer of all time.
It's Uncle Scrooge's fake-out.

Why is Uncle Scrooge
dressed like this?

Because he's smarter than
the smarties and disguisier
than the disguisies.
It's a work in progress.

Thanks for watching my
top disguises countdown.
Webby, where are you?
I'm invisible.
It's a disguise.
Man, she's good.
